WEBVTT

00:01.580 --> 00:04.490
Check it out. They got cars
that run on vegetable oil now.

00:04.500 --> 00:05.580
How about that.

00:05.590 --> 00:09.270
You know what would be cool? A
Hummer that runs on French fry grease.

00:10.250 --> 00:13.350
We could be energy independent
and still smash through crap.

00:13.370 --> 00:14.870
Sounds great.

00:14.890 --> 00:18.210
Plus, the new car smell is French fries.

00:18.220 --> 00:20.430
Okay, I'm only gonna
say this one more time.

00:20.450 --> 00:24.160
You don't get your license for two more
years and you're not getting a Hummer.

00:24.190 --> 00:27.730
You know, you say you want me to
open up to you, but what's the point?

00:32.860 --> 00:35.910
Yeah, I always loved
Paris in the springtime.

00:35.930 --> 00:36.900
Oh, you're lucky.

00:36.930 --> 00:39.800
I only got to do her once, on Halloween.

00:42.000 --> 00:44.020
Oh, hey, Alan.

00:44.040 --> 00:46.140
Andy, this is my
brother Alan. Alan, Andy.

00:46.150 --> 00:47.800
- Hello.
- Hey, Andy.

00:47.810 --> 00:49.890
Pull up a chair. We're
just telling war stories.

00:49.900 --> 00:51.610
Oh, great.

00:51.630 --> 00:53.880
- The sponge?
- Yeah.

00:55.300 --> 00:57.910
So, uh, how do you guys know each other?

00:58.640 --> 01:01.650
- Well, Andy and I--
- Can I have a cigar?

01:03.690 --> 01:06.140
- Sure, help yourself.
- Thank you.

01:07.140 --> 01:08.930
Anyway, Andy and I
have known each other--

01:08.940 --> 01:12.830
Maybe I'll take one for
now and one for later.

01:16.340 --> 01:21.490
Anyway, before he moved to New York,
Andy and I were partners in crime.

01:21.520 --> 01:23.230
There weren't that many actual crimes.

01:23.250 --> 01:26.380
Unless you count the
ones against nature.

01:26.390 --> 01:29.310
Alan, this is a great man.

01:29.340 --> 01:32.210
No, no, Albert Einstein was a great man.

01:32.220 --> 01:34.200
I just drink, gamble and hump.

01:34.210 --> 01:36.570
But I'm great at it.

01:36.580 --> 01:41.540
Andy once managed to hitchhike from
Vegas to L.A., wearing no pants.

01:41.550 --> 01:44.980
Hey, anybody can use their thumb.

01:45.960 --> 01:50.110
This right here, this is
the brother I never had.

01:50.120 --> 01:53.300
Oh, well, how nice for you.

01:53.330 --> 01:54.970
I don't mean it that way.

01:54.980 --> 01:57.050
- You're my brother.
- Well, thank you.

01:57.060 --> 02:00.260
I just like him better.

02:00.490 --> 02:01.510
Got it.

02:01.540 --> 02:05.830
Andy is the one guy in the world that can
match me drink for drink and broad for broad.

02:05.840 --> 02:07.630
In fact, the one time I thought
I drank him under the table,

02:07.650 --> 02:10.660
it turned out he had
a broad under there.

02:11.009 --> 02:13.820
Right, Andy?

02:14.680 --> 02:17.300
Andy?

02:17.770 --> 02:21.110
Don't screw with me, dude.

02:25.350 --> 02:27.540
Who's your favorite brother now?

